1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
DREAM is a Qwen Cloud MemoryAgent for source-backed engineering intelligence.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Engineering context is scattered across tickets, runbooks, code, incidents, PRs, and past decisions.

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:34,000
The architecture uses Qwen Cloud generation, governed memory, FastAPI, and Alibaba Function Compute packaging.

4
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Memory Hub makes source intake, parsed sections, review state, and evidence coverage visible.

5
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Knowledge intake promotes reviewed source cards and quarantines stale or unsafe claims.

6
00:00:52,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Retrieval traces show why docs, incidents, code, tests, Jira items, and PRs were selected.

7
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:10,000
DREAM turns retrieved memory into questions, impact maps, engineering briefs, and Jira-ready drafts.

8
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Audit and evaluation loops capture scores, source coverage, warnings, and human ratings.

9
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:25,000
DREAM turns scattered engineering context into persistent memory.

10
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Memory Hub keeps source intake, parsed sections, review state, and evidence visible.

11
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Knowledge intake promotes only reviewed source cards into reusable memory.

12
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Retrieval paths explain why docs, incidents, code, tests, Jira, and PRs were selected.

13
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Requirement workflows turn retrieved memory into review-ready Jira drafts.

14
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Runtime settings expose backend mode before local or Alibaba Cloud execution.

15
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:21,000
The proof chain validates Qwen config, Alibaba deployment files, CI, video, backend health, and final readiness gates.

16
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:31,000
DREAM remembers source truth, retrieves evidence, generates with Qwen Cloud, and proves deployment on Alibaba Cloud.
